An original ‘ autem ’ was not likely to have been corrupted into ⁴ cum ⁷ ; the adversative particle is quite superfluous and it is omitted in Puteolanus. ‘Cum' may possibly represent ‘cunctis’ or ‘omnibus‚' the compendium having been misunderstood (see crit. note c. 20 1). But, as an attributive of any kind is here both uncalled for and destructive of the libration of this adversative asyndeton, I prefer to delete ‘ cum ’ altogether, which is at least as justifiable and methodical as to change it to ⁶ autem.’
